Supplementary Materials for ‘Final title to insert’

Dragioti and colleagues

2022-09-24

Supplement S1: main analysis

Calculations

- Checking dataset formatting

view.errors.umbrella(dat, return = "messages")
## WARNING:
## - The confidence interval is not symmetric around the effect size (this is only a warning, not an error).

- Conduct main analyses

  • Between-study variance = Restricted maximum likelihood
  • Excess significance bias test = TESSPSST test
  • Small study effects test = Egger’s test
  • Within study correlation between outcomes = 0.8
umb <- umbrella(dat, method.var = "REML", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)

Stratification of the evidence

strat <- add.evidence(umb, criteria = "Ioannidis")

strat_pres = right_join(factor_data, summary(strat, het_max = TRUE, digits = 2)) %>%
  select(!Factor)
## Joining, by = "Factor"
DT::datatable(strat_pres, 
              rownames = FALSE,
              options = list(  # options
                initComplete = DT::JS(
                  "function(settings, json) {",
                  "$(this.api().table().body()).css({'font-size': '60%'});",
                  "$(this.api().table().header()).css({'font-size': '60%'});",
                  "}"),
                scrollX = TRUE,
                dom = c('ft'), 
                scrollY = "600px", 
                pageLength = 600,
                order = list(6, 'asc'),
                autoWidth = TRUE,
                columnDefs = list(
                  list(className = 'dt-center', 
                       targets = "_all"))))

Forest plot

source("functions_forest_plot.R")

forest.umbrella.name(strat,
       add_columns = factor_data_ord[,c("Meta_review", "Mental", "Physical")],
       measure = "eOR",
       main_add_columns = c("Meta-review", "Mental", "Physical"),
       max.value = 8,
       xlim_add_columns = c(-19.5, -14.5, -9), 
       xlim = c(-20, 5),
       pos_text = "center", 
       xlim_factor = -4, 
       print.classes = c("I", "II", "III", "IV"),

       cex_value = 0.8,
       cex_text_header = 0.8, 
       cex_value_header = 0.8, 
       cex_dots = 0.25,
       x_axis_adj = -1,
       factor_data = factor_data_ord
)

Supplement S2: Sensitivy analyses

1. Removing >1000 criterion

Stratification of the evidence

strat.s1 <- add.evidence(umb, criteria = "Personalized",
                      class_I = c(p_value = 1e-6, esb_p = 0.05, egger_p = 0.05, I2 = 50, pi = "notnull"),
                      class_II = c(p_value = 1e-6, largest_CI = "notnull"),
                      class_III = c(p_value = 0.001),
                      class_IV = c(p_value = 0.05), verbose = FALSE)

2. Diagnostic procedure

Calculations

umb.s2.SR1 <- umbrella(subset(dat, S2 == 1 & Factor != "88_analysis"), method.var = "REML", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)
umb.s2.SR2 <- umbrella(subset(dat, S2 == 1 & Factor == "88_analysis"), method.var = "DL", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)
umb.s2.SR = union.umbrella(umb.s2.SR1, umb.s2.SR2)
umb.s2.IR <- umbrella(subset(dat, S2 == 2), method.var = "REML", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)
umb.s2.MD <- umbrella(subset(dat, S2 == 3), method.var = "REML", method.esb = "TESSPSST", r = 0.8, mult.level = TRUE, verbose = FALSE)
